caller_intent: Che McDowell is seeking new homeowners insurance after his current USAA policy increased in price. He wants to compare options through Alliance Insurance Services.
resolution_steps: Brandi confirms Che is not a current client and begins gathering information.
Collects personal details (name, DOB, DL number, contact info, address).
Obtains co-owner (wife Sonya McDowell) information and mortgage provider (State Employees Credit Union).
Asks about property specifics (roof age, pools, pets, solar panels).
Discusses deductible options (confirms Che is comfortable with $2,500 deductible).
Informs Che that quoting team will contact him within the week.
knowledge_required: Process for initiating new policy quotes
summary: Che McDowell is shopping for new homeowners insurance after USAA rate increases. Brandi collects comprehensive personal and property information, confirms deductible preferences, and schedules follow-up from the quoting team. The call highlights carrier-specific deductible changes and the need for co-owner information.
